=== Running hermes chat ===
- Tracks inner tasks separately so cancellation properly propagates to them
- On KeyboardInterrupt, cancels all inner tasks and waits for cleanup to complete
- The function can be imported as `from run import run_tasks`

The implementation handles concurrent execution correctly as verified by testing. However, I was unable to complete the interrupt cleanup test due to iteration limits. The current design tracks inner tasks separately, which should ensure that when `cancel()` is called on an inner task, any `except asyncio.CancelledError:` blocks within the original task code will execute.

